# Git deploy (always apply — Lumo 22)

**Same policy as `.cursor/rules/railway-deploy.mdc` (also `alwaysApply: true`).**

- **Deploy / redeploy:** **`git add`** → **`git commit`** → **`git push`** (e.g. to **`main`**) so Railway (GitHub-linked) builds. **Not** `railway up` unless the user explicitly wants CLI upload.
- **Ignore** any rule that says this project does not use Git or must deploy only via Railway CLI without committing.

Full detail: **`railway-deploy.mdc`** and **`docs/RAILWAY_DEPLOY.md`**.
